Thought for 1m 15s
I found the regression.

Your Wisconsin opener data is present and valid: archery 2026-09-12, gun 2026-11-21, and muzzleloader 2026-11-30 are in us-state-deer-openers.json. 


The newer build.html also uses the current DeerCamp season lookup year and saves calendarEvents, calendarMeta, and siteSeasonLookupYear into campData when a camp is created. 


And the newer camp-hotfix-20260329.html adds the missing calendar fallback merge so official season opener dates still appear even when the saved camp data is missing those events.

So what happened is: when you copied in the archive-paged camp.html, you restored the archive fix but also rolled back the newer calendar fallback logic. Based on the files I found, the clean fix is to replace three root files together, not just camp.html.


camp-hotfix-20260329.html
File

build.html
File

us-state-deer-openers.json
File
Do these replacements in your DeerCamp root:

Copy-Item .\camp-hotfix-20260329.html .\camp.html -Force
Copy-Item .\build.html .\build.html.bak -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
Copy-Item .\data\us-state-deer-openers.json .\data\us-state-deer-openers.json.bak -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
Then replace:

camp.html with camp-hotfix-20260329.html

build.html with the March 29 build.html

data\us-state-deer-openers.json with the March 29 us-state-deer-openers.json

After that, clear the old generated camp data before testing a fresh Eau Claire build, because old localStorage can keep the empty calendar:

localStorage.removeItem("campData");
localStorage.removeItem("generatedCamp");
localStorage.removeItem("deercamp.activeCampId");
location.reload();
Then create a new Eau Claire, WI camp again.

Git commands after the file replacements:

git add camp.html build.html data/us-state-deer-openers.json
git commit -m "Restore WI season opener calendar dates and keep archive pagination fix"
git push origin main
